## Lab Setup Notes

- Use a separate API key per engagement; rotate after delivery
- Keep a "scratch" model account for genuinely risky experiments — some providers will warn / suspend on certain content; don't burn your main key
- For self-hosted, run inside an isolated VM with no production network access
- Save *all* prompts and outputs. Disk is cheap; reproducing a finding three weeks later from memory is not
- Anything you extract that might be real PII — write it down in a finding, encrypt the evidence, do not paste into Slack screenshots

