## Staying Current

The half-life of an AI security technique is short. Things that help:

- **Simon Willison's blog** (`simonwillison.net`) — running coverage of prompt injection developments
- **Embrace the Red** (`embracethered.com`) — practical exploit walkthroughs
- **AI safety institute publications** — UK AISI, US AISI (formerly NIST AISI under EO 14110; institutional form has shifted post-Jan 2025, check current status)
- **DEF CON AI Village** materials each year
- **Major lab blogs** — Anthropic, OpenAI, Google DeepMind, Meta AI publish red team research
- **AVID release notes** — new failure modes added regularly

---

That's the practitioner loop. Keep it tight, measure everything, write reports that respect the reader's time.
